    "This process can be formulated asΛ(y r (t, τ)) D1 ≷ D0 Γ,(5)where Γ 0 denotes the detection threshold, and D 1 and D 0 denote the decisions that radar infers H 1 and H 0, respectively.",
    "It can be observed from (2) that the echo signal is \"modulated\" by the target, which contains the critical parameters of the target, including range, velocity, and angle.",
    "Therefore, various algorithms have been developed to estimate these parameters by analyzing the echo signal.",
    "For example, pulse compression is a widely used range estimation algorithm [86].",
    "In addition, multiple signal classification (MUSIC) based on subspace decomposition is a high-resolution angle estimation algorithm [87]."
